properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 18 at 2:22PM EST until February 19 at 6:00AM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...South to southwest winds around 10 knots into this
evening, becoming northwest 10 to 15 knots with gusts up to 20
knots late tonight. Seas 4 to 6 feet are expected.

* WHERE...The coastal waters of Delaware.

* WHEN...Until 6:00 AM Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating a small
vessel, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM EST WEDNESDAY
